           <td><p style="color: 1589ff;"><span style="font-family: times new roman; color: #2d6cc0; font-size: medium;"><img class="img_L" title="3newgrants" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="New Materials Faculty Member" height="108" />New Materials Faculty Member<br /></span></p><span class="date"><span style="color: #d36006;">March 04, 2014</span> </span><br /><br />Dr. De-en Jiang has accepted a position at UC Riverside as an Assistant Professor of Chemistry and will be joining the department in July 2014. His research focuses on addressing important materials chemistry problems by computational tools.&nbsp; <a class="Morelink" href="http://chem.ucr.edu/faculty.html?id=219">Read More</a><img title="test" src="/images/design6/dividerline.jpg" alt="test" width="450" height="10" size="1" /></td>
          </tr>
          <tr> 
           <td><p style="color: 1589ff;"><span style="font-family: times new roman; color: #2d6cc0; font-size: medium;"><img class="img_L" title="3newgrants" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="New Organic Faculty Member" height="108" />New Organic Faculty Member<br /></span></p><span class="date"><span style="color: #d36006;">February 27, 2014</span> </span><br /><br />Dr. Dave Martin has accepted a position at UC Riverside as an Assistant Professor of Chemistry and will be joining the department in July 2014. His research will include the development of new catalytic transformations using abundant transition metals, novel strategies for bond activation including photochemical methods, and the synthesis of biologically active natural products.&nbsp; <a class="Morelink" href="http://chem.ucr.edu/faculty.html?id=218">Read More</a><img title="test" src="/images/design6/dividerline.jpg" alt="test" width="450" height="10" size="1" /></td>
          </tr>
          <tr> 
           <td><p style="color: 1589ff;"><span style="font-family: times new roman; color: #2d6cc0; font-size: medium;"><img class="img_L" title="3newgrants" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Mary Nguyen receives an Eli Lilly/WCC Travel Award" height="108" />Mary Nguyen receives an Eli Lilly/WCC Travel Award<br /></span></p><span class="date"><span style="color: #d36006;">February 10, 2014</span> </span><br /><br />Mary Nguyen (BS chemistry major) was one of only a few recipients nationwide of the Eli Lilly/WCC Travel Award for her ongoing research with Prof. Catharine Larsen. This highly competitive award supported her travel to the ACS National Meeting in Indianapolis where she gave both a poster and an oral presentation. Mary was also recognized at the Women Chemists Committee (WCC) Luncheon and invited to breakfast with Madeleine Jacobs, Executive Director of the ACS.&nbsp; <a class="Morelink" href="http://www.acs.org/content/acs/en/funding-and-awards/awards/other/travel/wcctravelaward.html">Read More</a><img title="test" src="/images/design6/dividerline.jpg" alt="test" width="450" height="10" size="1" /></td>

Mr. Weir has over 40 years of experience in the management, planning, operation, and maintenance of water, wastewater, and recycled water facilities. He currently serves as an independent consultant following nearly 20 years as General Manager for East Bay Dischargers Authority, which is a regional wastewater and recycled water agency serving over 600,000 residents in Alameda County, California. &nbsp; <a class="Morelink" href="http://chem.ucr.edu/news/alumni_news/chuck_weir.html">Read More</a><img title="test" src="/images/design6/dividerline.jpg" alt="test" width="450" height="10" size="1" /></td>

     <p align="center"><strong>Shanghai Jiao Tong University &amp; CE-CERT Student Symposium</strong></p> 
     <p>The ninth search symposium between Shanghai Jiao Tong University and University of California, Riverside took place on October 30<sup>th</sup>, 2013 at CE-CERT. The nearly decade long collaboration between the universities have generously supported by William Johnson of Johnson Machinery Company of Riverside. The exchange program serves to deepen students understanding of the research approaches of both universities.</p> 
     <p align="center"><em><img src="/photos/symposium2013.jpg" alt="symposium2013" width="600" height="400" /><br />Symposium at CE-CERT</em></p> 
     <p>Dr. Xinling Li (SJTU)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Effects of combustion parameters on diesel engine particle physic-chemical properties<em></em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p> 
     <p>Michael Giordano (UCR) <em></em>The Limitations of Electrical Mobility Diameter for Biomass Burning CCN Activation<em></em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p> 
     <p>Charles Cai (UCR)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Co-Solvent to Promote Biofuel Precursor Production from Biomass</p> 
     <p>Zhuoyaog He (SJTU)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em></em>Application of Biomass Derived Gases on Internal Combustion Engine<em></em></p> 
     <p>Jill Luo (UCR)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Deriving Macroscopice Black Carbon Emissions Factors of On-Road Traffic Using Roadside Measurements and a Dispersion Model&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p> 
     <p>Guan Chun (SJTU)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Changes of physico-chemical properties during ageing of diesel soot&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p> 
     <p>Chen Gu (SJTU)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em></em>In suit of DRIFTS study of the mechanism of low temperature SCR over manganese iron oxides prepared by SHS<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em></p> 
     <p>Zeyun Fan (SJTU)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em></em>Catalytic Oxidation Removal Technology of Formaldehyde at Low Temperature&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p> 
     <p>Amornrat Suemanotham (UCR)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em></em>Process Analysis of Microalgae-Based Biodiesel and Co-Product Production Using Steam Hydrogasification<em> </em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p> 
     <p>Chunhai Wang (SJTU)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em></em>Spray Behaviors of Gasoline-Diesel Blends in a Diesel Engine Common Rail System<em></em></p> 
     <p>Taehoon Lim (UCR)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em></em>Improving Performance of Dye-Sensitized Solar Cells by Solving Structural Limitation<em> &nbsp;</em></p> 
     <p>Yang Li (UCR)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>&quot;</em>Determination of Light-Duty Vehicles PM Exhaust<em>&quot;<strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></em></p> 
     <p><strong><em>&nbsp;</em></strong></p> 
     <p align="center"><img src="/photos/sjtuchamber2013.jpg" alt="chamber SJTU" width="600" height="400" /><br clear="ALL" /> <em>Tour of the Chamber</em></p> 
     <p align="center"><em><img src="/photos/mexcali2013.jpg" alt="Dinner SJTU" width="600" height="400" /></em></p> 
     <p align="center"><em>Dinner after the Student Symposium</em></p> 
     <p>Luckily, the Shanghai visitors were able to have an extra day dedicated to sight see. Jill Luo was able to take them to San Diego to visit the Air &amp; Space Museum. CE-CERT was honored to have them as guests and our graduate students are excited to visit their campus in Shanghai this coming year.&nbsp;</p> 
    </div>
